						               													<description>Valley of Fire&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is a fictional colonial campaign set in the Northwest Frontier during the late 1880s.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A British fort is under siege and a relieving force has exactly one month to break the siege! &amp;#10;The villages in the valley and mountain passes go into revolt, adding more and more forces to the siege and to block the British advance.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The system features hidden movement, is of moderate complexity, and is designed to be run with or without a referee.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The PDF contains:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     rules,&amp;#10;     counters,&amp;#10;     a planning map, and&amp;#10;     log sheets. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For a more detailed map, download the full version.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Although designed for use with The Sword and the Flame, this campaign can be used with any historical miniatures skirmish rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Turn Sequence:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Reinforcements Phase-Both sides determine if they receive any reinforcements. &amp;#10;     Revolt Phase:  Check all Afghan villages/tribal areas to see if any additional areas join the revolt. &amp;#10;     Initiative Phase-Determine the order of movement for the turn. &amp;#10;     Movement/Combat Phase-Forces of both sides conduct movement.  Battles take place in areas where forces of both sides occupy the same space. &amp;#10;     Combat Phase-Fort Phase-Assaults, sorties, and siege status  changes take effect. &amp;#10;     Admin Phase-Adjust supply totals, consolidate/split forces, etc. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
